EdgeGuard License
EdgeGuard is released under a dual-licensing model to support both open-source community use and commercial applications.
Open-Source License: GNU Affero General Public License (AGPL) 3.0
For individuals, non-profits, academic institutions, and other non-commercial users, EdgeGuard is licensed under the GNU Affero General Public License (AGPL) 3.0. This license allows you to freely use, modify, and distribute the software, provided that:

Any modifications or derivative works are also licensed under AGPL 3.0.
If you use EdgeGuard in a network service (e.g., cloud-hosted IoT platform), you must make the source code of the modified version available to users of that service.
The original copyright notice and disclaimer are retained in all copies or substantial portions of the software.

The full text of the AGPL 3.0 is available at: https://www.gnu.org/licenses/agpl-3.0.html.
Summary for Non-Commercial Users:

Free to use, modify, and distribute for non-commercial purposes.
Must share source code of modifications, including for network services.
Ideal for hobbyists, researchers, and open-source contributors testing EdgeGuard on devices like the Seeed Studio XIAO nRF52840 Sense for applications such as smart agriculture, weather monitoring, or logistics.

Commercial License
For companies seeking to integrate EdgeGuard into proprietary products or services without the obligations of the AGPL 3.0 (e.g., source code disclosure), a proprietary commercial license is available. This license allows:

Use of EdgeGuard in proprietary applications without sharing source code.
Access to premium features, such as MQTT/CoAP connectors (edgeguard-connectors), advanced Extended Kalman Filter models (e.g., IMU fusion), and enterprise-grade support.
Flexible integration for safety-critical IoT applications in industries like smart agriculture, logistics, medical IoT, and industrial IoT.

Pricing:

Commercial License: $2,000-$10,000/year, tiered by deployment scale (e.g., $2,000 for 1-10 devices, $10,000 for 100+ devices).
Premium Support: $200-$300/hour for consulting, $10,000-$50,000/year for support contracts, $5,000-$20,000 for fixed-term integration projects.

To inquire about a commercial license, contact colin@teraflux.app

